x4freetext: Experiment performed using UNILAC
accelerator and velocity filter SHIP at GSI Darmstadt
The targets were prepared from isotopically enriched
Pb-207. Layers of 380 mug/cm**2 thickness of the
chemical compound Pb-207-S have been evaporated on
carbon foils of 40 mug/cm**2  and covered by
10 mug/cm**2 carbon.
Velocity separator SHIP with crossed
magnetic and electric fields was used

reacs.QuantHlp: Differential c/s with respect to angle

x4freetext: fig.1c
*By author*. The double differential cross-sections are
related to the acceptance angle of the separator,
which is (0 +-2) degree and to the setting which leads
to optimized transmission of the respective transfer
product. Corrections for the transmission have not been
done, therefore, the cross-sections could be up to a
factor of two larger after correction. This is a rough
guess. The cross-sections in the table are given in
nb/sr. The beam energy is given in the centre-of-mass.
